Welcome to the casino!
Today you will be playing a game to earn tokens. </br> At the end of the experiment, you will be paid a bonus based on how many tokens you win.
On every turn, you will be shown four different decks of cards. </br> You need to select a card from one of the four decks.
On the next screen, you will see what the decks will look like.
You should pick a card from a deck using the '2', '4', '6', and '8' keys at the top of the keyboard.
Once you select a card, it will turn over and you will see how many tokens you earned.

Let's try practicing that! </br> First, try to put your fingers over the '2', '4', '6', and '8' keys. </br>  You can use whatever fingers are most comfortable for you. Try to find a comfortable position now.
Okay ready? </br> On the next screen, press '2' to select the left deck.
Great! Now on the next screen, try pressing '6' to select the third deck.
Now on the next screen, try pressing '4' to select the second deck.
Finally, try pressing '8' to select the deck all the way on the right.
Great! It seems like you are getting the hang of this.
You may have noticed that some cards will cause you to win tokens while other cards will cause you to lose tokens.
Each deck has a mix of cards that will cause you to win and lose tokens. </br> However, the cards in each colored deck are different.
Some colored decks are luckier than others. </br> If you choose the lucky decks, you will earn more tokens than if you choose the unlucky decks.
You should try to figure out which decks are lucky. </br> Then, try to choose the lucky decks so you can win the most tokens.
To make it trickier, the casino dealer will switch the locations of the decks on every turn. </br> The color of the deck determines how lucky it is. The location does not matter.
The mix of cards in each colored deck will stay the same throughout the game. </br> That means that a deck that is lucky early on will stay lucky.
Remember though, all the decks have a mix of both good and bad cards so it may take a couple of turns to figure out if a deck is lucky.
At the end of the game, you will be paid bonus money based on how many tokens you win. </br> If you win more tokens, you will earn more money!

You will never lose money.
If you end up with fewer than 0 tokens, you will earn $0 of bonus money, but you will still be paid for playing the game.
You will have 10 seconds to make each choice.
Before you play the game for real, you will play with practice decks. </br> The tokens you earn during practice won't count toward your total.
Ready? Remember, use the '2', '4', '6', and '8' keys to select the decks. </br> Put your fingers on those keys now and then press '2' to begin.
You earned 900 tokens during the practice round!
Nice job! You are almost ready to play the real game.
You will play two rounds of the real game. In each round, you will pick 100 cards in total.
We are now going to ask you some questions about how the game works.
Answer carefully. You will not be able to begin the game until you answer them correctly.
True or False: All the decks have some cards that cause you to win tokens and some cards that cause you to lose tokens.
False is incorrect. All the decks have a mix of winning and losing cards.
True or False: All the decks have some cards that cause you to win tokens and some cards that cause you to lose tokens.
True is correct! All the decks have a mix of winning and losing cards.
True or False: You will have as much time as you want to make your response.
False is correct! You will only have 10 seconds to make each choice.
True or False: The location of the deck determines how lucky it is.
True is incorrect. The color of the deck determines how lucky or unlucky it is.
True or False: The location of the deck determines how lucky it is.
False is correct! The color of the deck determines how lucky or unlucky it is.
Great job! Now it's time to start the real game.
Before we start, we're going to head into a new room of the casino.
Here we are! The real game will use different cards, but the rules will be the same.
Ready? Put your fingers over the '2', '4', 6', and '8' keys so you are ready to play the game. </br> Then press 2 to start.
Take a break.
You earned 1820 tokens in the first round!
